# Trivy CVE suppression list
#
# Format: one CVE per line. Add `# expires:YYYY-MM-DD` and a justification.
# Mirror entries into docs/dependency-debt.md (Trivy table) so the
# rationale survives lint of this file.

# === Go stdlib CVEs in the pgvector:pg16 base image ===
# Trivy detects a Go-built binary inside the upstream pgvector image
# (likely gosu, used by the postgres entrypoint for user switching).
# We don't build or vendor this binary, so we can't bump its Go toolchain.
# The CVE class is std-library DoS / memory exhaustion / cert validation
# in network-input handling — the gosu binary doesn't take network input,
# so reachability is effectively zero for our runtime. Re-evaluate once
# pgvector publishes an updated image.
CVE-2025-58183  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib archive/tar DoS in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2025-61726  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib net/url DoS in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2025-61728  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib archive/zip DoS in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2025-61729  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib crypto/x509 DoS in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2025-68121  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib crypto/tls cert validation in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2026-25679  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib net/url IPv6 parsing in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2026-32280  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib crypto/tls DoS in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2026-32281  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib crypto/x509 DoS in pg16 base gobinary
CVE-2026-32283  # expires:2026-05-26 — go stdlib crypto/tls key-update DoS in pg16 base gobinary
